      "content": "I hear you on the systemic stuff, but it feels like you're saying deterrence is a total myth. Even if it's not perfect, isn't there some merit to the idea that certain laws make people think twice? It seems a bit extreme to just call it a \"fallacy\" and dismiss the whole concept of punishment as a way to maintain order.",
